# {DOMAIN} Skillify

Turn completed work into a reusable capability without cluttering the workspace. One-off output stays
in `work/`; repeated or maintained work becomes a staged, verified skill in `plugin/skills/`.

## Steps
1. **Confirm it should become a skill.** Ask: will this repeat, need upkeep, or prevent a failure from
   recurring? If no, keep the artifact in `work/{project}/YYYY-MM-DD-…/`, capture any reusable lesson
   in `knowledge/`, and stop.
2. **Prove provenance.** Identify the accepted result, source artifact, conversation, or failure that
   justifies the skill. Do not synthesize from vague memory.
3. **Name + triggers.** Choose a short kebab-case skill name and 3-5 trigger phrases a future user or
   agent would actually say.
4. **Stage first.** Draft in `work/YYYY-MM-DD-skillify-{name}/`; never write a half-working skill
   directly into `plugin/skills/`.
5. **Extract the repeatable process.** Keep the invariant steps, decision rules, examples, and reusable
   assets. Remove false starts, chat fragments, and one-off facts.
6. **Separate judgment from exact work.** Put the workflow and decision rules in `SKILL.md`. Put
   mechanical or deterministic work in `scripts/`, `assets/`, or templates only when it removes real
   repetition.
7. **Verify before publishing.** Use the strongest cheap check for the domain: a script test, smoke
   command, sample prompt replay, fixture comparison, checklist dry run, or review rubric. Record what
   passed in the staged folder.
8. **Ask before committing.** Show the proposed skill name, triggers, destination, and verification
   result. Move to `plugin/skills/{name}/` only after approval. **Unattended runs (e.g. a scheduled
   janitor, no human present):** do not publish — leave the verified draft in `work/` and log a proposal
   to `operations/improvements.md` for later approval. Publish to `plugin/skills/` only with explicit
   approval, or when the workspace declares an explicit autonomous-publish policy.
9. **Publish + repackage.** Move the staged skill into `plugin/skills/`, then re-zip `plugin/` to the
   delivery path (a transient artifact — never an `outputs/` folder inside the workspace) and update
   `operations/.packaged-version` so `{DOMAIN}-doctor` sees a fresh package. Update plugin README/index
   if present, and note any changed routine in `operations/`.
10. **Capture the learning.** If the skill came from a failure or important decision, write a short
    note to `knowledge/` so future agents understand why the skill exists.

## Quality bar
- No skill without a real source result or failure.
- No half-working skill in `plugin/skills/`.
- No one-off deliverable promoted just because it was useful once.
- No domain facts invented by the agent; mark assumptions "draft — confirm".
